      "message": "Ah, the classic \"delete from a linked list\" problem.  To avoid special-casing the first item, I have a good tip: Use a double-pointer.\n\nfor (TempFile** nextPtr \u003d \u0026all_tempfiles; *nextPtr; nextPtr \u003d \u0026(*nextPtr)-\u003enext) {\n    TempFile* tempfile \u003d *nextPtr;\n    if (!strcmp(tempfile-\u003ename, filename)) {\n        *nextPtr \u003d tempfile-\u003enext;\n        tempfile_close(tempfile);\n        free(tempfile);\n        return;\n    }\n}\n\nNot tested, but based on this stackoverflow post: https://stackoverflow.com/a/12915035",
